sentences: Edith Wiens OC (born 9 June 1950) is a Canadian opera, recital and concert singer with a soprano voice.
Wiens, daughter of a Mennonite pastor, grew up in Vancouver where she finished high school at the age of 16.
Her international career started in 1980 when the Berlin Philharmonic engaged her.
Wiens had her operatic debut in 1986 at the Glyndebourne Festival as Donna Anna in Mozart's Don Giovanni under Bernard Haitink.
Wiens is now a member of the faculty at the Juilliard School in New York City.
In 2011 the Internationale Meistersinger Akademie was founded, of which she is the artistic director.

The alumni of this summer academy, as well as her students from Juilliard, sing in major opera houses such as the Royal Opera House London, Metropolitan Opera New York, Munich, Hamburg, Dresden, Leipzig, Geneva, the Aalto Theatre in Essen, Zurich, Vienna, Frankfurt, Stuttgart, etc.
She was invested an Officer of the Order of Canada in 2000.
